Ms. L. T. Loi , born in 1962 (member #  010117090035). She farms, raises pigs and does selling at the market. Her husband is a hired worker. They have 4 children (2 are grown and employed, 2 are still in school). Average income for her family is 14 - 16 USD per day. Her family joined the fund to borrow 307 USD with the intention of expanding their business of raising pigs. She is the leader of her loan group, and the other members consist of:
 
Mr. Ngo V. G., born in 1986 (member # 010117090036). He is employed as a hired worker. He lives with his parents and they have stabL. income. His father is a hired worker; his mother sells breakfast food. Average income for his family is 17 USD per week. His loan amount is 284 USD to invest in raising animals;
Ms. Trinh T. L., born in 1969 (member # 010117090037). She has a clothing shop; her husband is a hired worker and a farmer. She and her husband have 2 children of school age. Average income for her family is 17 USD per week. Her loan amount is 210 USD to have money for making purchases for her shop;
MS. Do T. L., born in 1962 (member # 010117090038). She works in farming, and her 2 children are employed. Average income for her family is 14 USD per day. Her loan amount is 210 USD with the intention of raising animals;
Ms. Nguyen T. C., born in 1972 (member # 010117090039). She works in farming and selling at the market. She and her husband have 4 children. Average income for her family is 14 USD. Her loan amount is 284 USD to invest and expand business of raising animals;
Ms. Nguyen T. G., born in 1969 (member # 010117090040). In addition to farming, she does selling at the market. Her husband is a construction worker, her 2 children are still of school age. Average income for her family is 14 USD per day. Her loan amount is 210 USD for raising animals and selling at the market;
Ms. L. T. T. H., born in 1971 (member # 010117090041). She sells breakfast food, her husband is a hired worker, their 2 children are of school age. Average income of her family is 17 USD per day. Her loan amount is 260 USD to invest in her business;
Ms. Nguyen Q. T., born in 1985 (member # 010117090041). She has a clothing shop with average income of 17 USD per day. Her loan amount is 210 USD to invest in her clothing shop

 
 
 
 
 .
 
<br /><p><strong>Translated from Vietnamese by T. Ostrander, Kiva Volunteer</strong></p>

The group of borrowers consists of four people. Its leader, Mrs. Im S., 44, makes a living selling various grocery products, such as cooking ingredients, plastic products, and sweets. She started the business six years ago, and currently earns approximately US$3 per day. Her husband is a motorcycle taxi driver. Mrs. Im S. has five children, one of whom is married, while the other four are still single and live with their parents. One of the daughters assists Mrs. Im S. at selling groceries. Currently, the family is suffering from pollution surrounding their house, which is harmful for their health. Therefore, Mrs. Im S. is requesting loan to purchase another piece of land.
The other three borrowers include Srey P., 36, who is a housewife and also needs a loan to buy a piece of land;
Chhea M., 31, who sells groceries and needs money to purchase an additional stock of groceries; and Som K., 26, who is widowed and earns a living selling groceries and needs a loan to expand her business. All of the borrowers live in Slor Kram Commune, Siem Reap Province.
